<HEADLINE> Mugabe: Zimbabwe's Education System Should Be </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- An education review commission
will soon be appointed in Zimbabwe to look into the effectiveness
of the the country's education system, said Zimbabwean President
Robert Mugabe here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ruling ZANU (PF) National Consultative
Assembly meeting, Mugabe said the present education system is not
yielding the desired results.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''For a good number of our people, the education that
we gave them has not rewarded them with a job.''
</P>
<P>
' As a result, it has become increasingly clear that a major
need in our educational system is that of skills training,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
He is also concerned about the increasing incidences of
HIV/AIDS and other diseases such as malaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
