<HEADLINE> US Endorsing Jerusalem as Israeli Capital Condemned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today condemned the United States for its move to
recognize Jerusalem as Israeli capital.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure for Turkey to attend a summit of Islamic
countries, Rafsanjani said that Washington's conspiracy to
recognize Jerusalem as capital of Israel will be discussed at the
summit of the eight Islamic developing states (D-8).
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said "the impudent move of the U.S. House of
Representative to shift the American embassy to Bait-al-Moqaddas
(Jerusalem) indicated Washington's disregard for the world of
Islam and Arab states."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the U.S. made the move at a time when its
influence in the Middle East is at a low ebb.
</P>
<P>
"The holding of the D-8 summit of Islamic states in Turkey has
acquired greater significance in view of the U.S. conspiracy and
we should get prepared to defend the sanctities of the world of
Islam," he said, quoted by the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
Heads of Iran, Turkey, Indonesia, Pakistan, Malaysia,
Bangladesh, Egypt and Nigeria are to hold a summit in Istanbul on
Sunday to study the grounds for comprehensive cooperation in the
world of Islam.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president said the eight states with a combined
population of 800 million people in addition to their vast
natural resources and geographical situation would endeavor to lay
the groundwork of constructive cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud
Mohammadi today strongly condemned the recognition by the
U.S. House of Representatives of Jerusalem as capital of Israel
as a move to encourage Israeli expansionism and escalate Middle
East crisis.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Islamic states to defend the interests of the
world of Islam against the unprincipled policies of the United
States and Israel, saying that the decision of the U.S. House of
Representatives unveiled the real face of those claiming to be
impartial in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi charged the U.S. House of Representatives with
trampling upon the religious rights of the Moslem world.
</P>
<P>
He warned the Israeli regime against hurting the religious
feelings of Moslems and violating the rights of the innocent
Palestinian people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
