<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Wins Gerry Weber Open Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia defeated
Petr Korda of Czech to win his first title of the year at the
Gerry Weber Open tennis tournament in Halle, Germany on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a thrilling seesaw game, the top seed Kafelnikov spent two
hours and 20 minutes to edge the Czech player, 7-6 (7-2), 6-7
(5-7), 7-6 (9-7).
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, ranked sixth in the world, ran his record to 10-2
in tie break sets this year at the 875,000 U.S. dollars Wimbledon
tuneup.
</P>
<P>
Korda, coming back from a serious groin injury, led 6-5 in the
final set after breaking the Russian's serve for the first time in
the match.
</P>
<P>
But Korda displayed nerves as he lost the following game with
three double faults.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov's 12th career title earned him 122,000 U.S. dollars
while Korda took home 72,400 dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
