<HEADLINE> Philippoussis Wins Queen's Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Mark Philippoussis
overwhelmed Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia 7-5, 6-3 to win the
Queen's grass-court tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the hard-fought game, 20-year-old Philippoussis racked up 15
aces and positioned himself and a genuine threat on grass when
Wimbledon Open will begin in a week.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, a two-time runner-up at Wimbledon, had 12 aces in a
match that offered little more than power serving.
</P>
<P>
It was the third victory this season for Philippoussis and his
second career win over Ivanisevic in as many matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
