<HEADLINE> Croatia Votes in Presidential Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 15 (Xinhua) - Croatian citizens on Sunday went to
polling stations to cast their votes for the second presidency of
the country since its independence in 1991.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7,558 polling stations have been established for
more than four million eligible voters, including 158 polling
sites for citizens abroad. The domestic stations opened at 07:00
local time and will close at 19:00 local time.
</P>
<P>
On the list of presidential candidates are incumbent president
Franjo Tudjman, Zdravko Tomac of the Social Democratic Party and
Vladimir Gotovac of a nine-party coalition.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman, who is revered as "the Father of Croatia", is widely
expected to win the reelection bid even in the first round,
according to some opinion polls which gave him 60 percent of the
votes.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman was elected president of Croatia before its
independence in 1990, and was re-elected in 1992 in the country's
first direct voting for presidency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
