<HEADLINE> 3 Palestinians Wounded in Clashes with Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 15 (Xinhua) -- At least three Palestinians
were injured this morning during clashes between Israeli
soldiers and Palestinian demonstrators in the West Bank town of
Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported that the clashes erupted when
dozens of Palestinian youngsters started to throw stones and
fire-bombs at Israeli soldiers guarding the Jewish quarter of
Beit Hadassah in downtown Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers and border police fired rubber bullets and
tear gas at the demonstrators to disperse the crowd, reportedly
injuring three Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Today's clashes came after a six-hour confrontation in the
city between Israeli soldiers and Palestinian protesters Saturday
when at least 30 Palestinians were wounded.
</P>
<P>
A series of clashes erupted between Israeli soldiers and
Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza Strip since the United
States Congress adopted a resolution Wendesday recognizing united
Jerusalem as Israel's capital.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) cabinet
issued a statement blaming the U.S.resolution. PNA chief
Jerusalem representative Faisal Husseini warned that if the
U.S. approves the resolution, "the whole peace process will be
lost."
</P>
<P>
Jordan's King Hussein, who is currently visiting Europe,
Friday criticized the U.S. resolution on Jerusalem, which, he
said, somewhat undermined the U.S. role in Middle East peace
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks between Israel and the Palestinians have been
stalled since March when Israel started to build a controversial
new Jewish neighborhood at Har Homa (Jabal Abu Ghneim) on the
southeastern outskirts of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians have said that Israel must stop the construction
before talks can resume, while Israel is insisting that the PNA
must crack down on terror and reestablish full security
cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
