<HEADLINE> Sino-Pak Mountaineers Scales Nanga Parbat Successfully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A China-Pakistan expedition
today successfully scaled 8125-meter-high Nanga Parbat Mountain
from the Diamer side, the expedition leader Sam Druk told Xinhua
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The expedition's summit team, which comprised six Chinese and
two Pakistani mountaineers, reached the summit at 11:15 am (local
time).
</P>
<P>
They hoisted national flags of China and Pakistan on the top of
the second highest mountain in Pakistan which ranks the ninth in
the world.
</P>
<P>
This is the first ascent of Nanga Parbat by the Chinese
mountaineers.
</P>
<P>
The 13-member expedition, seven Chinese and six Pakistanis, was
organized jointly by China Tibet Mountaineering Association (CTMA)
and Alpine Club of Pakistan to commemorate the Golden Jubilee of
the independence of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In a congratulatory message from Nanga Parbat base camp, the
expedition leader Sam Druk, member of the CTMA, stated that the
success is a gift to the people of Pakistan on the occasion of the
Golden Jubilee.
</P>
<P>
The success is also a gift to the people of his motherland on
the return of Hong Kong to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
