<HEADLINE> Alboreto Wins Le Mans Motor Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Former Ferrari Formula One driver
Michele Alboreto of Italy gave the privately entered Tom
Walkinshaw built Porsche prototype its second successive Le Mans
motor race victory in Le Mans, France on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Alboreto, whose previous best ever finish in Le Mans had been
eighth, took the lead just over two hours from the end when the
front running works Porsche 911 GTI of Ralk Kelleners burst into
flames.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf McLaren driven by France's Jean-Marc Gounon was
second, two laps behind, followed by the McLaren BMW of Peter Kox.
