<HEADLINE> Writers, Artists Urged to Produce Good Cultural Works for People (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official has told
the country's literary and art workers to work hard and produce
works of higher quality and provide the people "with the best
cultural sustenance".
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, head of the Propaganda Department of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the remark
at a "national conference on creating more fine literary and art
works" held here last week.
</P>
<P>
Ding, also member of the Political Bureau and the Secretariat,
of the CPC Central Committee, stressed that all the goals should
be achieved through adhering to the literary and artist policies
of "serving the people, serving the socialist cause," and "letting
a hundred flowers blossom and a hundred schools of thought
contend."
</P>
<P>
"And the laws governing literary and art creation shall be
fully complied with and work of writers and artists shall be fully
respected," Ding said.
</P>
<P>
He said that since Chinese President and CPC Central Committee
General Secretary Jiang Zemin made an important speech last
December on the work of literature and art, writers and artists
have given full play to their initiatives, and increased their
sense of responsibility for the society, and have written more
fine works of high political and moral standards.
</P>
<P>
"The current trend is very good," Ding commented.
</P>
<P>
But much remains to be done to create more works to inspire the
public, he said, adding that this is the need of reinvigorating
national spirits, the reform, opening up and the socialist
modernization, the development of socialist cultural market and
resistense against decadent ideological and cultural influences.
</P>
<P>
Ding pointed that while focusing on the purposes of serving the
people, reform and opening up, writers and artists should
diversify their creative forms, themes and styles, to match the
colorful life of the people.
</P>
</TEXT>
