<HEADLINE> UNDP Urges to Close Gender Gap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The united Nations Development Program
(UNDP) has urged developing countries to close gender gap so that the
energy and productive capabilities of women can be unleashed
for national development.
</P>
<P>
Developing countries should commit themselves to gender equality
if they are to eradicate poverty by the 21st centuary, said the 1997
Human Development Report available from the UNDP office in Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
In developing countries, illiterate women outnumber men by 60
percent and that women still have less access to employment
opportunities, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that such trends should be reversed if developing
nations are to eradicate poverty and achieve sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Developing countries which will achieve economic
growth in the next five years are those that have made poverty
eradication a priority and give women more access to political and
professional opportunities, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
