<HEADLINE> Entrepreneurship among Leaders of Rural Enterprises Encouraged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun
today urged Township entrepreneurs to improve their overall
quality so as to promote essential changes of their businesses.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also a member of the Political Bureau of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), said that
township enterprises are facing good opportunity as well as
rigorous challenges under new circumstances, while meeting with
representatives of China Association of Young Township
Entrepreneurs (CAYTE) here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that township enterprises have become the most vital
economic sector in rural areas of the country since China
initiated reform and opening up policy in late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
He said that tasks for township entrepreneurs are to grasp the
spirit of the national conference on township enterprises held
earlier this year, and implement the Law on Village and Township
Enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Township entrepreneurs, he stressed, should upgrade step by
step the management, technological and service levels of their
enterprises. The overall quality of township enterprises should be
promoted so that they could fit in with market demand and market
competition, the vice-premier said.
</P>
<P>
The development of township enterprises is considered a
strategic choice of China to make the country prosperous and its
people well-off.
</P>
<P>
The CAYTE, set up in 1988, is a national organization for
excellent young township entrepreneurs. Incomplete statistics
showed that about 40 percent of CAYTE members are leaders of large
or medium-sized township enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
