<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Slams U.S. for Embassy Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani today accused the United States of trying to move its
embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem, a controversial
city between Israelis and Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the first D-8 Group summit in Turkey's largest
city of Istanbul, Rafsanjani strongly slammed the adoption of a
resolution by the U.S. Congress last Wednesday concerning the
transfer of the U.S. Embassy in Israel, describing it as "a
flagrant violation of the inalienable rights of the Palestinian
people."
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said that Iran was deeply concerned about the
U.S. move, saying "it illustrates once again that U.S. policy is
completely dedicated to serving the illegitimate interests of
Israel."
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president called on the Islamic world and the D-8
Group to make appropriate reaction in response to the U.S. embassy
transfer resolution.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani is an enthusiastic supporter for the D-8 Group
sponsored by Islamic Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan late
last year.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 Group summit, which has attracted presidents, prime
ministers as well as other senior officials from the eight
Muslim developing countries, today officially announced the
establishment of the bloc.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 groups Bangladesh, Egypt, Indonesia, Iran, Malaysia,
Nigeria, Pakistan and Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
