<HEADLINE> Million Dollar FIFA Grant for Developing Asian Football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Asia has secured a one
million U.S. dollar grant from world football body FIFA to develop
the game in the region, Asian Football Confederation general
secretary Peter Velappan said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The grant, for the years 1999 to 2003, will be used to "train
coaches, develop youth programmes and to purchase equipment for
the respective countries," Velappan added.
</P>
<P>
The AFC would evaluate the requirements of each of its
affliates and produce a five-year development programme, he said.
</P>
<P>
The general secretary said the AFC would boost the FIFA grant
with its own donation of 500,000 dollars which would be added to
by contributions from rich AFC affliates such as Japan, Qatar and
Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Velappan noted the AFC held a one week seminar in Kazakhstan on
communications, administration and training schemes to educate
referees, coaches and medical officers.
</P>
<P>
He said Asia's booming economies would further boost the game
in the region. 
</P>
