<HEADLINE> Harbin Trade Fair Opens Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The 8th Harbin Economic and Trade
Fair opened today in the capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province. More than 3,600 business people from more than 50
countries and regions attended the event.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang province has a border of more than 3,000
kilometers with Russia, and 25 ports open to the country. The
participants in the fair, come from Russia, other countries in the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), some east European
countries, Japan, the Republic of Korea, and more than 20 domestic
provinces and municipalities. They set up 800 exhibition stands,
including 100 foreign stands, at an exhibition hall covering an
area of 16,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
On display were more than 20,000 varieties of commodities in 20
categories, such as farm and sideline products, food, light
textile products, machinery, electronics, medical and health care
products, and daily necessities.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang put forward nearly 1,000 projects for investment
from and cooperation with overseas and domestic counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Since the first Harbin trade fair opened in 1990, contracts
valued at an accumulated 30 billion US dollars were signed at the
events, making the fair one of the four largest in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
