<HEADLINE> Fiji Beats Papua New Guinea in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Fiji defeated Papua New Guinea
3-1 in a soccer World Cup Oceania Zone Group 2 qualifier in Suva,
Fiji, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Fiji sprinted to a 2-0 lead at half-time and Papua New Guinea
pulled one back in the second half before Fiji scored its third
goal.
</P>
<P>
The victory means that Fiji, which lost to New Zealand 1-0 in
the first round, remained in contention in the group. The team
will face New Zealand in the group decider in Auckland on
Wednesday.
