<HEADLINE> Bank Loans to Help Nepalese Women End Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A Nepal Bank Ltd. branch has
started distributing loans to help lift women in this Himalayan
kingdom out of poverty with the assistance of the Asian
Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
Under a women's small credit project implemented by the
government, women who have received basic training in savings and
loans and who have formed into savings groups are provided loans
without collateral, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
With the loans, women are encouraged to be involved in income
generating activities, so as to uplift themselves out of poverty
both socially and economically.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government has listed poverty eradication within a
given time frame through pro-poor growth and employment-friendly
programs as an overriding objective of the upcoming Ninth Five
Year Plan (1997-2002).
</P>
<P>
The poverty of women arrests in particular the attention of the
government, since Nepal is one of the two exceptional countries in
the world with life expectancy of women less than that of men.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Nepalese women lag far behind men in literacy,
access to education, health services, land and credit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
