<HEADLINE> Nigerian Civil Servants to Stage Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Civil servants in northern Nigeria's
Kaduna State have been urged to begin an indefinite strike from
tomorrow, the Sunday Vanguard reported today.
</P>
<P>
The directive for strike comes from the Kaduna State
Public Service Negotiating Council, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The civil servants are demanding the payment of a 50 percent
increase in their awards and allowances for medical, transport
and accommodation approved by the government about four years
ago, according to the report said.
</P>
<P>
The council advised the government to maintain security to
safeguard public property, as all watchmen are expected to fully
participate in the industrial action.
</P>
<P>
The council decided to go on strike after the expiration of a
21-day ultimatum persuading the government to meet its demands.
