<HEADLINE> 1.2 Million Children in Shenyang Join Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 1.2 million children, or
one-fifth of the total population in Shenyang, northeast China's
biggest city have insurance coverage of various kinds.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey, more than 500,000 children have
benefited from insurance compensation, involving a total of 125
million yuan (15 million US dollars) in payments.
</P>
<P>
Since the practice was introduced in the city 11 years ago, 11
types of insurance have become available for children, including
life, health, and accident insurance.
</P>
<P>
A student living in the city's Dadong District who was badly
burned in an explosion of a cooking pot, was asked to pay 80,000
yuan (9,600 US dollars) for medical treatment. His insurance
company paid 75,000 yuan for his medical expenses and gave him
another 6,000 yuan in compensation.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 380,000 preschool children and 120,000
middle and primary school children in the city have benefited from
insurance. 
</P>
