<HEADLINE> OAU Calls for Peaceful Resolution of Congo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has called on parties in the crisis of the Republic
of Congo to seek a peaceful solution.
</P>
<P>
The OAU Central Organ of the Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention, Management said that parties involved should
"scrupulously observe the ceasefire and commit themselves to a
peaceful resolution of the crisis through dialogue and
negotiations."
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the OAU here today, the
central organ met in an extra-ordinary session at ambassadorial
level on June 14 at the request of Victor Nimi, permanent
representative of Congo to the OAU.
</P>
<P>
The central organ expressed its deep concern over the deterio-
rating situation in the Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
The central organ expressed its full support for the mediation
efforts currently undertaken by Hadj Omar Bongo, President of
Gabon and urged all concerned to extend their support and full
cooperation to president Bongo's efforts.
</P>
<P>
The central organ reaffirmed its full support for the
principle of showing respect for all constitutional institutions
of the state in Congo and expressed its principled opposition to
any attempt to undermine those institutions which are the
embodiment of the sovereign and democratic will of the people.
</P>
<P>
It condemned the existence of private armed militias in the
country and called for their immediate disbandment to create a
conducive environment for the holding of democratic elections at
an appropriate future date.
</P>
<P>
It also appealed for urgent humanitarian assistance to be
extended to all those in need.  
</P>
</TEXT>
