<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Province Speeding up Market Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Business turnover in a broad
range of markets in north China's Hebei Province is expected to
rise to 130 billion yuan this year, up from 114 billion yuan in
1996.
</P>
<P>
This is a result of the local effort to expand existing markets
into high-quality and multi-functional undertakings, and to add
new ones.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 4,549 trading markets, 154 of which have
more than 100 million yuan in annual turnover each.
</P>
<P>
Thirty of them, which deal in industrial products, means of
production, pharmaceuticals and fur and leather, have up to 1.7
billion yuan in annual turnover each.
</P>
<P>
This year the province plans to expand and add 100 markets so
as to increase the number of the markets with trade volume
exceeding 100 million yuan each to 180.
</P>
<P>
The province will also give a boost to the development of
markets in rural areas and set up a number of businesses involved
in the wholesale of farm and sideline products, which will be
supplied to nearby cities such as Beijing and Tianjin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
