<HEADLINE> Poem on Deng Xiaoping Dubbed with Music </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- "Song for Deng Xiaoping," a
3,000-line poem lauding the late Chinese leader, has been dubbed
with music and made into an audio cassette.
</P>
<P>
The China Record Company Shanghai Branch, producer of the
cassette, plans to promote the cassette both at home and in
overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
The company also gave the cassette as a gift to Guang'an County
of southwest China's Sichuan Province, Deng's hometown.
</P>
<P>
The poem, written by Shanghai poet Gui Xinghua, 49, famous for
his political themes, consists of six parts: "Prelude," "Chief
Architect," "The Road of Exploration," "Economic Reform," "Great
Changes of China" and "Hong Kong, Oh, Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
The music was based on the theme song of the 12-part TV
documentary "Deng Xiaoping." Some of China's well-known artists,
such as Xi Meijuan, Zhang Mingyu, Wang Jianxin, Zhao Qi'ou, Wang
Hongsheng, Zhang Pei read the lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
