<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade in Shanghai Pudong New Area Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area in Shanghai
saw its foreign trade volume rise 28 percent on an annual basis to
3.266 billion US dollars during the January-May period.
</P>
<P>
The zone's import volume rose 26.3 percent to 1.71 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Customs figures show that Pudong's imports and exports are
dominated by machinery and electronic products. Imports of these
rose 49 percent to 589 million US dollars, while exports soared 80
percent to 517 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone's foreign trade volume with Japan was 775 million US
dollars during the first five months of the year, up 21.4 percent
on a yearly basis, making Japan the zone's biggest foreign trade
partner.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's second major foreign trade partner is the United
States. Their trade volume amounted to 479 million US dollars, an
increase of 46.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong ranks third, with a total trade volume of 273 million
US dollars with Pudong. This represented an increase of 22.2
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
