<HEADLINE> Japan Retains Kirin Cup Football Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Japan defated Turkey 1-0 victory in
the final match in Osaka on Sunday to win Kirin Cup football
tournament title for the third year running.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Hiroaki Morishima scored the winning goal in the 25th
minute of the match.
</P>
<P>
Japan were unbeaten with two wins, while Turkey and Croatia had
a draw and a loss each in the three-team competition.
</P>
<P>
The Japaese team, whcih won 60,000 U.S. dollars for winning the
tournament, defeated Croatia 4-3 a week ago in Tokyo, while
Croatia and Turkey drew 1-1 in Sendai on Thursday. 
</P>
