<HEADLINE> CPPCC Leader Meets Hong Kong Entrepreneurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The policy of "One Country, Two
Systems" to be implemented in Hong Kong will play an exemplary
role for the issue of Taiwan, a senior CPPCC leader said today.
</P>
<P>
Wan Guoquan, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made
the remark at a meeting with a group of Hong Kong entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
He said that the central government will give full support to
Hong Kong's development after China resumes the exercise of
sovereignty over the region on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In the past, Hong Kong made contributions to the development of
the inland areas through mutual economic exchanges and promotion,
and the region's development was also backed by the inland areas,
Wan said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the political, social, and economic situation is
very good in both Hong Kong and the inland areas, and people's
living standards are improving, which provides a solid foundation
for Hong Kong's continuous prosperity and stability in the future.
</P>
<P>
Wan emphasized that all the Chinese people should
unconditionally abide by the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region. 
</P>
