<HEADLINE> China Regarded as Most Important Nation by Japan, U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China has been regarded both in
Japan and the United States as the most important foreign country
in their diplomatic relations for the next two decades, said a
survey published today in the Nihon Keizai Shimbun.
</P>
<P>
The leading Japanese economic newspaper said 55.6 percent of
Japanese respondents and 32 percent of U.S. respondents picked
China as the most important country in diplomatic relations for
the next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The telephone survey, jointly conducted in May by the Nihon
Keizai Shimbun and the Wall Street Journal, covered 1,200 Japanese
and 1,204 Americans, all aged 18 or older. 
