<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Meets American Sepecial Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 15 (Xinhua) --Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa yesterday held talks with U.S. special envoy on the
situation in the Great Lakes.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the State House, at their
talks, Mkapa and the U.S. special envoy on Great Lakes, Howard
Wolpe, reviewed the situation in the Central and East African
region, the security and stability in particular.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that concerted international as well as
regional efforts should be continued to strengthen peace and
security in the Great Lakes Region, especially in Burundi and the
Democratic Republic of Congo. 
