<HEADLINE> Ramos to Start Trip to Europe, Middle East Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
will leave here tomorrow for a nine-day trip to Europe and the
Middle East "in pursuit of his administration's economic
diplomacy," the presidential office said today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the office said Ramos will be in
Britain from June 16-20, Oman on June 21-22 and Greece on June
22-24, and he will have talks with leaders of the three countries.
</P>
<P>
The trip to Britain is considered as "a working visit" while
his tour of Oman and Greece are "state visits," it said.
</P>
<P>
The president will be accompanied by his wife, Foreign
Secretary Domingo Siazon, Trade and Industry Secretary Cesar
Bautista, Press Secretary Hector Villanueva and two senators and
four congressmen, the office said.
</P>
<P>
A business delegation composed of leaders of some of the
Philippines' top corporations will also be with the presidential
entourage, it said. 
