<HEADLINE> Zambians Urged to Support Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Vice-President Godfrey
Miyanda has appealed the people to provide foreign investors with
a sound environment, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
In a recent speech in Kitwe of Copperbelt province, Miyanda
said there is no country in the world which can succeed without
foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors could not stay in the country if they are
not supported by the local people, Miyanda added.
</P>
<P>
As for foreign investors, the vice-president said that they
should not come to the country and disappear after making a
fortune, adding that they should do their best to win the support
from the public.
</P>
<P>
Miyanda said that foreign investors should help the state
convince the general public that they are here to help develop
the country. 
</P>
