<HEADLINE> Internet Surfing at Hotel Room </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The ability to surf the
Internet from hotel room may become another way of attracting
guests for the hotels, along with the mini bar, swimming pool and
cable TV.
</P>
<P>
According to today's Hebrew daily Ma'ariv, Israel's Hashmira
Protection Technologies firm has started the new "in-room
Internet" service this week with the American Colony Hotel in
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
All hotel guests can use the service to surf the Internet in
their rooms, without specially ordering it in advance, and will
pay at checkout.
</P>
<P>
The in-room Internet also offers a variety of in-house
services, including wake-up calls, ordering films and TV computer
games, room service and preparing the bill for checkout.
</P>
<P>
The firm's managing director Gideon Ben-Shmuel said that the
in-room Internet boosts hotel services into a new league, adding
it is easy to install and operate.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the in-room Internet system will be
offered to hotels around Israel, especially those with many
guests from the United States and Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
