<HEADLINE> De la Hoya Keeps Title with Second Round Knockout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Oscar de la Hoya displayed some
impressive punching power on Saturday in knocking out David Kamau
of Kenya in the second round to retain his World Boxing Council
(WBC) welterweight title.
</P>
<P>
De la Hoya knocked down Kamau early in the second round and put
him down again with six seconds left to improve his perfect record
to 25-0, while handing the Kenyan challenger only his second loss
in 31 professional fights.
</P>
<P>
On the first knockdown, de la Hoya dropped Kamau with a short,
hard left hook to the head.
</P>
<P>
Late in the round, the two again exchanged big punches before
de la Hoya unleashed a head-snapping left hook to the side of the
head that left Kamau stunned on his feet for a few seconds before
he fell over backwards.
</P>
<P>
Kamau tried in vain to get up and was counted out by the
referee at 2:56 of the second round. 
</P>
