<DOCNO> XIE19970615.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Press Center for HK Handover Ceremony Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Press and Broadcast Center
(PBC) for the Hong Kong Handover Ceremony and related events was
officially opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Located on the 7th floor of the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center (HKCEC), the PBC is closely connected with the
major venue for the Handover Ceremony -- the HKCEC Extension.
</P>
<P>
The PBC, occupying an area of 9,000 square meters, includes a
broadcast center for TV and radio broadcasters and a press center
for the print media. The two centers operate around the clock
starting from 10:00 am today till 6:00 pm on July 10.
</P>
<P>
The press center has approximately 600 seats for journalists'
free use and some 85 separate journalist working booths which have
all been booked out.
</P>
<P>
The broadcast center has some 150 working rooms. In addition,
one studio, two edit suites, tape transfers and dubs and other
facilities and services are also bookable for broadcasters.
</P>
<P>
"It's the first time in our history Hong Kong is providing a
media center on this scale and complexity to media organizations
from all over the world," said Thomas Chan, director of
information services, at a ceremony opening the press center early
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Handover Ceremony Coordination Office said
the PBC is well equipped with phones, faxes, computer connection
access points, video walls, Internet service, photo processing and
all other necessary facilities and services.
</P>
<P>
In the coming weeks, over 8,000 journalists from all over the
world will use the PBC as their base in reporting the historic
occasion.
</P>
<P>
"The number of journalists who applied to come are some 2,000
more than we had expected, but we are still able to provide
sufficient facilities and services for them," said Felix Cheng,
principal information officer of the Handover Ceremony
Coordination Office.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
