NEW DELHI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Steering Committee of
India's ruling United Front (UF) is expected to meet on Monday to
take a final review of the vexed issue of hiking prices of
petroleum products, the Sunday Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The issue has been discussed at length at the committee's two
previous meetings recently, but no consensus could emerge as the
left parties in the 16-party UF stoutly resisted any move by the
government to raise prices of petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
The government is heavily burdened with a financial deficit
caused by subsidized prices of oil products, and favors a price
hike in oil products to reduce the deficit.
</P>
<P>
The Monday meeting will also discuss the UF's position on the
coming presidential election for which nominations close on June
23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
