<HEADLINE> EC Imposes Anti-dumping Duty on Indian Bed Linen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) has
imposed provisional anti-dumping duty on bed linen exports from
India and two other countries, the Sunday Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The duty, which was imposed on Friday, ranges between 3.9
percent and 27.3 percent and has to be ratified by the European
Union (EU) Council of Ministers within six months.
</P>
<P>
Normally one month is given for filing objections, but this
time the affected parties have been asked to do so within 15 days,
industrial sources said here.
</P>
<P>
Anti-dumping duties have also been imposed on Pakistan and
Egypt and the duty averages 13.6 percent.  
</P>
