<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Exports To Sweden Doubled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's exports to Sweden rose
from 4.45 million U.S. dollars in 1991 to 8.92 million U.S.
dollars in 1996, according to a local press report today.
</P>
<P>
The report said a development program initiated by Sri Lankan
Export Development Board (EDB) and implemented under a contract
between Sri Lanka's Chamber of Commerce and the Swedish
International Development Agency contributed to the increase in
exports to Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The program was designed to develop the two export-oriented
sectors of rubber and textiles.
</P>
<P>
This year, Sri Lanka has received orders from Sweden worth
400,000 U.S. dollars, of which nearly 50 percent were from new
contacts.
</P>
<P>
The EDB has also launched similar programs in other European
markets such as Germany, Italy, the Netherlands and Switzerland.
</P>
