<HEADLINE> Foreign Experts Helping Develop Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners are working for more
than 130 key State projects and about 500,000 foreign-funded
enterprises, today's China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
Of the 80,000 foreign experts in China every year, about 25,000
work for key State projects and 30,000 for foreign-funded
enterprises. They install equipment and provide technical guidance
and managerial consulting.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, imported technology and equipment approved by the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Co-operation reached 13.1
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
About ten percent, or 1.3 billion dollars, is for technical
services including foreign experts. Although the figure seems
large, the direct and indirect benefits are worth the price, the
paper quoted Miao Mantian, a division chief of the State Bureau of
Foreign Experts Affairs' economic and technical experts
department, as saying.
</P>
<P>
With help of foreign experts, some key State projects began
operating on time or ahead of schedule, saving money.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China has learned advanced technology and managerial
experience and has gained trained domestic professionals, Miao
said.
</P>
<P>
Miao said that the State Bureau of Foreign Experts Affairs will
work out regulations on management of foreign experts this year,
and will select 100 key State projects and 100 foreign enterprises
to improve management of foreign experts.
</P>
<P>
Last August, the bureau designated Hubei and Sichuan provinces,
Shanghai, Qingdao, and the China National Offshore Oil Corp. to
pilot management of foreign economic experts. And the work will be
expanded on the basis of experience, Miao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
