<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hall of HK in Great Hall of People Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin recently
wrote an inscription to mark the completion of the Hall of Hong
Kong of the Great Hall of the People, which will be officially
open after July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He wrote, "Carry out the principle of one country, two systems,
and maintain the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong." The
inscription has been carved on a giant Oriental screen in the main
reception room of the Hall of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Located in the southwest part of the Great Hall of the People,
the Hall of Hong Kong covers an area of 1,728 square meters, and
is the largest of all the 32 halls representing China's provinces,
autonomous regions or municipalities there.
</P>
<P>
The hall has two parts: a main reception room and a
multi-functional room. An 818-square-meter garden is on the roof.
</P>
<P>
The design of two entrances and two rooms of the Hall of Hong
Kong is unique in the Great Hall of the People, as the
significance of the return of Hong Kong is reflected in the
architectural details.
</P>
<P>
An embroidered tapestry will be placed on the wall of the
reception room, depicting Victoria Harbor at night. In the
corridor outside the multi-functional room is a group of
sculptures of white dolphins, symbols of celebration of the return
of Hong Kong. The copper mural in the multi-functional room
reflects the 100-year changes since the Opium War.
</P>
<P>
"To come here seems to return home," said a Hong Kong visitor
when viewing the hall during construction.
</P>
<P>
The building of the Hall of Hong Kong caught the attention of
tens of millions of people, and it has also been a dream of the
Hong Kong compatriots for years.
</P>
<P>
Chairmen of various terms of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, Peng Zhen, Wan Li, and Qiao Shi, all
emphasized the importance of the establishment of the Hall of Hong
Kong in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hall of the People is the site of China's important
political and diplomatic activities. Late Premier Zhou Enlai said
that each administrative region of China will have a hall in it.
Therefore, the new Hall of Hong Kong is an important symbol for
the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The proposal to establish the Hall of Hong Kong was first made
in 1985 by Fei Yimin, a Hong Kong deputy to the National People's
Congress. During the National People's Congress last year, Henry
Fok Ying-tung took the lead to form a group that would carry out
the preparatory work for the hall.
</P>
<P>
After soliciting opinions from experts from both Hong Kong and
the inland areas, the project was started last June. During the
construction, dozens of alterations have been made to the design,
in order to fully reflect the characteristics of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch,
said that as Hong Kong is a special administrative region, the
design of the Hall of Hong Kong should be unique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970615.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
