<HEADLINE> Special Bus Service Introduced in Nepali Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A special bus service has been
introduced in schools in Nepal with a view to making travel to and
from school safe and comfortable for children.
</P>
<P>
The so-called Skyline Bus Service has been designed and
developed jointly by Eicher Motors Ltd India and the Indian
Institute of Road Traffic Education, press reports here said
today.
</P>
<P>
The diesel engine-buses have various facilities such as extra
racks for school bags, water bottles below the seats and first aid
boxes. It can signal approaching vehicles that children are
embarking and disembarking.
</P>
<P>
