<HEADLINE> Stimulants Seized in Myanmar Border Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities have seized
10,000 tablets of Rama stimulants recently in Tachilek, Myanmar's
Shan state bordering Thailand, the official newspaper New Light of
Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The tablets in five packets were found hidden in a local
villager's belt when he was intercepted by local military
intelligence units and an anti-drug squad on June 3.
</P>
<P>
Another villager was also arrested in connection with the case,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly six million tablets of methamphetamine stimulant drug
were confiscated in Myanmar-Thai border areas in 1996, according
to Myanmar anti-drug sources.  
</P>
