<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Clinch Spanish Title in Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Real Madrid won their 27th
Spanish league title in fine style on Saturday with an
impressive 3-1 victory over reigning champions Atletico.
</P>
<P>
Needing just a point, Real tore their neighbours apart with
first half goals from Raul Gonzalez and Fernando Hierro. Predrag
Mijatovic added the third shortly after the break.
</P>
<P>
Atletico coach Radomir Antic made a triple-substitution
after Mijatovic's goal and was quickly rewarded with a goal from
former Real striker Juan Eduardo Esnaider.
</P>
<P>
After the match, Real president Lorenzo Sanz took the
opportunity to announce that Tenerife coach Jupp Heynckes will
almost certainly take the place of the Italian Capello, who is
returning to his former club AC Milan next season, to occupy the
hot seat at the Bernabeu stadium.
</P>
<P>
In the 36th minute of the match, the Real teenager Raul
Gonzalez controlled a difficult cross from the left and worked his
way into position before unleashing a powerful shot into the net.
</P>
<P>
Just before half-time Real went two-up when Atletico goalie
Molina was left standing by a free-kick from Hierro that caught a
deflection.
</P>
<P>
The game was sealed in the 56th minute when Clarence Seedorf
sliced open a sleepy Atletico defence before feeding the ball to
Mijatovic to score. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
