<HEADLINE> Mutlu, Italian Swimmers Top First Day of Med Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Turkish weightlifter Halil Mutlu
claimed two gold medals and the host country dominated in the
swimming pool Saturday as the 13th Mediterranean Games got
underway.
</P>
<P>
Mutlu, an Olympic champion and world record holder, won both
the snatch and the clean-and-jerk in the 54-kilogram (119-pound)
division to take the first medals awarded in this southern port
city.
</P>
<P>
At the pool, Italians came away with half of the eight golds
and 10 medals overall.
</P>
<P>
These Games, the largest ever with nearly 3,500 athletes from
21 countries competing in 27 sports - all records - are somewhat
of a litmus test of Italy's ability to organize a big sporting
event. Rome is one of five finalists for the 2004 Summer
Olympics, and 21 IOC members are here. 
</P>
