<HEADLINE> Price of Venezuelan Oil Keeps Dropping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the
Venezuelan basket of crudes and oil by-products for export closed
Friday at 14.95 U.S. dollars per barrel, dropping 0.97 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Statistics of the Ministry of Energy and Mines showed that the
average price kept under the 14.90 dollars per barrel since
Monday, and on Thursday, it even dropped to 14.76 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The price maintained 17.23 dollars per barrel for the first
five months this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the basket of the seven crudes exported by the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) registered an
0.82 dollars decline and ended at 16.91 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts foresee a recovery of the international oil
quotations between August and October, with the increase of demand
of the industrialized countries for their winter necessities.
</P>
</TEXT>
