<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Beats Paraguay in Copa America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, Ecuador, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador beat World Cup
qualifying leader Paraguay 2-0 in the first round of the Copa
America at Cochaabamba, Bolivia, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Wellington Sanchez scored off a free kick in the 71st minute
while second-half substitute Ariel Graziani made it 2-0 15 minutes
later.
</P>
<P>
The victory put Ecuador to the top of the Group A with four
points from two matches. Paraguay is second with three points.
The group also includes Argentina and Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970615.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poles Rediscover Goalscoring Touch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Poland breezed past Georgia 4-1 in
their World Cup European zone group two qualifier on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Poland, who stay third in the group eight points behind
second-placed England, made the most of their opportunities to
score their first goals in four World Cup qualifiers this year,
despite going a goal behind in the 24th minute.
</P>
<P>
Georgia striker Shota Arveladje found the net from an acute
angle but Poland struck back quickly with goals in the 33rd and
35th minutes by Adam Ledwon and Miroslaw Trzeciak.
</P>
<P>
Captain Krzysztof Bukalski added a penalty in the 70th minute
and Krzysztof Nowak tapped in a cross a minute from the end to
complete the scoring.
</P>
<P>
Poland fielded a drastically reshaped squad in their first game
under head coach Krzysztof Pawlak, who took over from Antoni
Piechniczek following Poland's 2-0 loss against England last
month, which ended their chances of advancing to the finals in
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
